    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<head>Mac. to Monsieur Paul A. Rockwell <date value="1916-09-09">September 9th 1916</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline><date value="1916-09-09">September 9th 1916</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Paul:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            This damn business is
            getting discouraging.  My back, while
            it is some better seems awfully 
            slow in coming around and if
            they’ll let me I want to go back
            with it as it is for I can at
            least sit in an aeroplane with
            it.  My other trouble is practically 
            O.K.  Hope to be out anyway in
            a week or ten days at the outside
            but will need to do some walking
            around and eating to get into
            any condition.  The nice part about
            it is that they are going to
            arrange that for me.  The Medicine
            Chef himself saw me yesterday and
            said he’d give me two months
            convalescence if I wanted.  I told him
            I only wanted a few days so as
            to get used to seeing something
            besides a line of beds and to
            eat something besides eggs and
            milk.  Therefore James will breeze
            down for a short reunion within
            not so many days and I’ll be damned
            
            <pb n="[p.2]"/>
            
            glad to see you.
            </p><p>
            I inclose [sic] the check I spoke
            of that my mother sent me.  Will
            you be so kind as to watch for
            a favorable day of exchange and cash
            it then for me, hanging onto the 
            money until I get down or need
            some here.
            </p><p>
            My uniform never has shown
            up any place.
            </p><p>
            I see your spiel about me
            came out all right.  Got a cable
            from my mother this morning.
            </p><p>
            Just like America not to protest
            against Lille outrage, isn’t it?  Even 
            Brazil did.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>Hope you are feeling fine.
            <lb/>
            Yours</salute>
            
            <signed>Mac.</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            Hopital Mixte<lb/>
            Vitry le Francois.<lb/>
            Marne.
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
            <!-- [The envelope with this letter is addressed to Monsieur Paul A. Rockwell, 80 Rue Boissiere, XVI, Paris.] -->
            
            </div1>
